    <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <h1>SHA-256 vs SHA-512: Which Hash Algorithm Should You Use?</h1>

      <p>SHA-256 and SHA-512 are both members of the SHA-2 (Secure Hash Algorithm 2) family, designed by the NSA and published by NIST in 2001. They are the most widely used cryptographic hash functions today, but they differ in output size, internal structure, and performance characteristics. This comparison helps you choose the right algorithm for your use case.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/tools/hash-generator" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-primary)] px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-colors hover:opacity-90">Try Hash Generator →</a>
      </div>

      <h2>Quick Comparison Table</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-secondary)]">
              <th class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Feature</th>
              <th class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">SHA-256</th>
              <th class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">SHA-512</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Output Size</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">256 bits (32 bytes)</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">512 bits (64 bytes)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-secondary)]/50"><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Hex Output Length</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">64 characters</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">128 characters</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Internal Word Size</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">32-bit words</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">64-bit words</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-secondary)]/50"><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Block Size</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">512 bits</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">1024 bits</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Rounds</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">64</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">80</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-secondary)]/50"><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Collision Resistance</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">2<sup>128</sup></td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">2<sup>256</sup></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Performance (64-bit CPU)</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">Slower</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">~30-50% faster</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-secondary)]/50"><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5 font-medium">Performance (32-bit CPU)</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">Faster</td><td class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2.5">Slower</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
